{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban body shaming in the media",
        "additional_details": "A recent example was passed around Twitter of a participant on Love Island in a bikini, the media had posted this photo trying to portray that she didn't look good, and this attracted so many vile comments about her body.\r\n\r\nThe shaming from bullies and trolls is being encouraged by some news outlets because they are posting these photos and articles.\r\n\r\nThese images and comments are so dangerous and damaging, in particular when aimed at young females.\r\n\r\nThis needs to stop!",
        "background": "Require all media organisations and advertisers to prevent body shaming and reflect the diversity and reality of people's bodies, and give press and media regulators the power to regulate this. As part of that, it should be illegal to publish images of people\u2019s bodies without their consent. ",
